<DOC><DOCNO> AP881123-0108 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-23-88 1128EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-USSoldiersKilled     11-23 0163</FIRST><SECOND>PM-US Soldiers Killed,0165</SECOND><HEAD>Three U.S. Soldiers Killed in Training Accident</HEAD><DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Three U.S. soldiers were killed ina nighttime training operation in Bavaria when their tank fell intoa pit and overturned, the U.S. Army reported today.   The accident Sunday night at the Hohenfels military traininggrounds also injured another soldier, Army spokesman 1st Lt. PatrickSawyer said in a telephone interview from 3rd Infantry Divisionheadquarters in Wuerzburg.   Sawyer identified the dead soldiers as: Capt. Donald M. Kessler,31, of Canton, Ga.; Staff Sgt. James Frear, 30, of Deridder, La.;and Spec. Anthony T. Tallos, 20, of Philadelphia. Pvt. Dean C. Brownwas released after being treated for minor injuries, Sawyer said.   The accident occurred when the men inadvertently drove the tankinto a pit normally used as a fighting position for militaryvehicles during combat maneuvers, Sawyer said.   Army authorities are investigating the accident.   The Hohenfels military training area is 75 miles northwest ofMunich.</TEXT></DOC>